{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"coaching":[{"coaching":"State the concrete attestation evidence the [operator-attested] anchor-recording proof mechanism will require (a change id / vote outcome / timestamp), recorded on the ticket.","decision":"block","finding_refs":["fb5ecb2ef394073d1"],"move_id":"14","move_name":"state attestation evidence","subject":"anchor-recording proof mechanism"},{"coaching":"Plan how per-event grandfathered flag capture path will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f436898cedb16eac3"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"per-event grandfathered flag capture path"},{"coaching":"Test the riskiest assumption behind AC1 dependency on upstream signing stories first.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f0e0706ed1ff7003b"],"move_id":"4","move_name":"riskiest-assumption test","subject":"AC1 dependency on upstream signing stories"}],"coverage":{"counts":{"advisory_overflow":0,"advisory_surfaced":1,"blocking":1,"dropped":6,"indeterminate":0},"det":{"P1":{"ac_items":3,"blocking":false,"clarity_score":7,"name":"readiness-shape","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P2":{"blocking":false,"name":"resolution","probed":2,"ran":true,"references":2,"resolved":2,"status":"pass","unresolved_or_abstained":0},"P3":{"blocking":false,"name":"package-existence","packages":0,"ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P4":{"ac_items":3,"blocking":false,"desc_chars":4368,"file_impact":3,"name":"oversize","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P5":{"blocking":false,"children":0,"name":"task-dag","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P6":{"ac_items":3,"blocking":false,"name":"ac-quality","ran":true,"status":"pass","verify_commands_linted":52,"verify_lint_abstained":52},"P7":{"blocking":false,"destructive_hits":[],"name":"destructive-sniff","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P8":{"blocking":false,"budget_tokens":868000,"name":"reviewability","plan_tokens":1111,"ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P9":{"applicable":true,"blocking":false,"file_impact":3,"name":"file-impact-coverage","ran":true,"status":"pass"}},"floored_criteria":["COH","E1"],"floored_finding_ids":["f0e0706ed1ff7003b"],"llm_ran":true,"metrics":{"claim_path":"no-llm/no-network (structural; the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify)","det_ms":201.1,"llm_calls":28,"llm_ms":319004.0,"total_ms":319354.9,"verify_requests":13},"narrowed":true,"remediation":{"baseline":"signature","eligible":true,"reasons":{"code_unchanged":true,"plan_changed":true,"prior_sidecar":true,"registry_unchanged":true,"signed":true,"within_window":true}},"routing":{"agent_tier":["A1","E4","G1G2","G6","G7","T1","T10","T11","T13","T14","T3","T5c","T8","removal-rationale"],"single_turn":["COH","E1","E2","E3","E5","E6","F1","F4","G5","T2","T4","T5b","T5e","T6","T9","hedge"]}},"findings":[{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Tag the 'anchor recorded on ticket' sub-criterion as `[operator-attested]` (per ADR 0043) and add a concrete attestation artifact (e.g. ticket comment URL or change-id) as the proof, OR add an in-session check such as asserting the SHA exists in `git log --oneline tickets` output.","cohort":["E2","E6","F1"],"criteria":["E6","F1"],"decision":"block","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'The 40-hex boundary SHA (an existing tickets-branch commit, NOT the flip commit) + its rationale are recorded as a comment on this ticket.'","Proving command given is only: 'git diff --stat origin/main..HEAD -- rebar.toml shows no change'","No command checks that the anchor comment actually exists on the ticket."],"finding":"AC3's positive claim — 'the 40-hex boundary SHA + rationale are recorded as a comment on this ticket' — has no in-session proving command; only the negative (`git diff --stat ... rebar.toml`) is verifiable in-session.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fb5ecb2ef394073d1","impact":0.85,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — AC3","norm_id":"nce2874af48490ab0","priority":0.7285,"reason":"high-priority+criterion-opted-in","scenarios":["The story could be marked done with rebar.toml untouched but the anchor SHA never actually recorded, satisfying the mechanical check without satisfying the intent.","Story 8d39, which must consume the anchor verbatim, has no machine-verifiable dependency edge."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"Prepend `[operator-attested]` to the 'anchor recorded' sentence in AC3 and specify that the done-evidence is a ticket comment containing the 40-hex SHA, so reviewers know exactly what to look for.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.8571,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"low","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Clarify the test's output-capture mechanism: either (a) use subprocess + `--format json` + `json.loads(res.stdout)` to assert per-event `grandfathered` flags (matching the pattern in `test_identity_ac7_bff8_heldout.py`), or (b) specify the stdout-redirection approach needed to inspect the JSON report from an in-process `verify_authorship.cli()` call.","cohort":["G6"],"criteria":["G6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan: 'Uses the established harness (repo fixture, _keypair, forge recipe, in-process verify_authorship.cli)'","Plan: 'assert: overall exit non-zero (post-boundary enforced), the pre-boundary entry has grandfathered: true, the post-boundary entry grandfathered: false'","verify_authorship.cli() signature returns int (exit code only); structured per-event report is emitted to stdout","test_identity_ac7_bff8_heldout.py uses subprocess + '--format json' + json.loads(res.stdout) to access grandfathered fields — not in-process cli()"],"finding":"The plan's test spec says 'in-process `verify_authorship.cli`' AND 'assert per-event `grandfathered` flags', but `cli()` returns only an int (exit code). Capturing per-event grandfathered flags from an in-process call requires redirecting sys.stdout and parsing `--format json` output — a non-trivial mechanism the plan leaves unspecified. The existing comparable test (`test_identity_ac7_bff8_heldout.py`) sidesteps this by using subprocess+JSON. If the implementer naively calls `cli([...])` in-process and tries to inspect per-event flags without stdout redirection, the assertion cannot be written as described.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f436898cedb16eac3","impact":0.85,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section / regression test description; AC line: 'assert per-event `grandfathered` flags in a single mixed store' and 'Uses … in-process `verify_authorship.cli`'","norm_id":"n37abddbdf4096a96","priority":0.5312,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Implementer calls `rc = verify_authorship.cli(['--all', '--require-authenticated', '--since', sha, '--root', str(repo)])` in-process and finds no way to inspect per-event grandfathered flags from rc alone.","Implementer attempts stdout redirection (e.g., io.StringIO + monkeypatch of sys.stdout) but --format json also writes the summary to stderr, making the capture fragile."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"Replace 'in-process verify_authorship.cli' with subprocess invocation using '--format json', then parse stdout with json.loads — consistent with test_identity_ac7_bff8_heldout.py and directly assertable on per-entry 'grandfathered' fields without any stdout-capture machinery.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"low","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"low","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Replace `<slug>` with a concrete, decided filename (e.g. `test_identity_enforce_since_boundary.py`) everywhere it appears in the plan so the proving command is literally executable.","cohort":["E2","E6","F1"],"criteria":["E2","E6"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'pytest tests/unit/test_identity_enforce_since_<slug>.py -q'","The test file name is also a placeholder in the What section: 'tests/unit/test_identity_enforce_since_<slug>.py'"],"finding":"The pytest proving command for AC2 contains an unresolved `<slug>` placeholder (`pytest tests/unit/test_identity_enforce_since_<slug>.py -q`) that cannot be executed as written; an agent cannot run it without first deciding the filename.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f8071a41c41b20a7d","impact":0.44,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — AC2 proving command","norm_id":"n4589ae40a71d5069","priority":0.165,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["An executing agent running CI verification cannot invoke this command literally.","A reviewer cannot confirm the correct file was produced without a canonical name."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Choose a fixed name such as `test_identity_enforce_since_boundary.py` and use it consistently in both the What section and the AC2 proving command.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify in the test description that per-event `grandfathered` flags are asserted against the structured output artifact (name the key/format, e.g. JSON result dict) using an exact-key assertion, not a substring/prose match.","cohort":["E2","E6","F1"],"criteria":["E6"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'assert per-event grandfathered flags in a single mixed store'","'the pre-boundary entry has grandfathered: true, the post-boundary entry grandfathered: false'","No mention of output format (JSON, TOML, prose) or assertion tool (jq, Python assert, grep)."],"finding":"The plan specifies asserting 'per-event `grandfathered` flags' in the regression test but does not state whether the assertion targets structured output (e.g. JSON via `jq -e`) or prose/log text, leaving the assertion method ambiguous and prone to false-positives on substring matches.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fb4881e9deb010763","impact":0.44,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section — regression test description; AC2","norm_id":"nd6ccd847742abc6e","priority":0.165,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["A grep-based assertion on prose output can match a substring in a log message unrelated to the actual event record.","If the output format changes, the test silently mis-asserts without a schema-anchored check."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Add a sentence such as: 'Assert `result.events[i][\"grandfathered\"] == True/False` directly on the return value of `verify_authorship.cli(...)` called in-process, or parse the structured JSON output with `jq -e`.`","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Persist the decided anchor SHA in a durable, in-repo artifact (e.g., a small markdown file under `docs/` or a git note on the chosen commit) so 8d39 can verify it without relying solely on the ticket comment.","cohort":["E3","T6","T9"],"criteria":["T9"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["\"Record the chosen 40-hex SHA + rationale on this ticket for 8d39 to consume verbatim\"","The anchor lives exclusively as a ticket comment; no in-repo file (e.g., docs/enforce_since_candidate.txt or a git note) is created as a fallback.","If the ticket comment is lost or mis-copied, 8d39 has no canonical machine-readable source to fall back on."],"finding":"The anchor SHA is recorded only as a human-readable ticket comment — there is no durable, machine-discoverable artifact in the repo — so 8d39 could consume a stale or missing value if the ticket is edited, deleted, or simply overlooked by the implementer.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f3896a63ef0a827d8","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What > 'Decide and document the enforcement-boundary anchor' / AC3","norm_id":"na9ff191bd8ba1949","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["Ticket comment is edited or lost between stories; 8d39 author copies the wrong SHA; the anchor value is unverifiable without re-running the manual `rebar verify-identity` check."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add a step: after the anchor is verified with `rebar verify-identity --all --require-authenticated --since <candidate>`, write the 40-hex SHA to `docs/enforce_since_anchor.md` (committed to the `tickets` branch or `main`) so 8d39 can `cat` it rather than copy-paste from a ticket.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Retitle or add a clarifying note to the title/scope: the 'repin' in this story means DECIDING and RECORDING the anchor value (not writing it to rebar.toml), and make the artifact that proves 'decided and recorded' explicit in the AC.","cohort":["E3","T6","T9"],"criteria":["E3"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Title: 'Verify and repin identity.enforce_since so pre-flip events are grandfathered'","Scope: 'this story does not modify rebar.toml (verified: the change touches only the new test file under tests/)'","AC3 proving command: 'git diff --stat origin/main..HEAD -- rebar.toml shows no change'"],"finding":"The title says 'repin identity.enforce_since' but this story explicitly does NOT write enforce_since anywhere in the codebase; the 'repin' is only a decision recorded in a ticket comment, which could mislead implementers about what 'done' means for this story.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f5c4f445d3fa1f156","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Title / Scope section / AC3","norm_id":"n12e51bc90718be22","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["An implementer reads the title and expects enforce_since to be written in this story, then discovers nothing in rebar.toml changed and wonders if the story was completed; or, reviewing the PR, an approver expects the pin to be present and rejects the PR as incomplete."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Rename to 'Verify grandfathering logic, add regression test, and decide enforce_since anchor for 8d39' — or add a sentence to the Scope section: \"'Repin' in the title means selecting and recording the anchor SHA; the actual rebar.toml write is 8d39's responsibility.\"\n","tier":"LLM","validity":0.2857,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["E6"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The proving command for AC2 contains an unresolved `<slug>` token, making it non-executable as written — a command with a literal angle-bracket token will fail before testing anything.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f0e56e2fb251ef5e5","impact":0.44,"is_primary":null,"location":"AC2 proving command: 'pytest tests/unit/test_identity_enforce_since_<slug>.py -q exits 0'","norm_id":"n85c6983ef620a108","priority":0.165,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":[],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Use `pytest tests/unit/test_identity_enforce_since_boundary.py -q` (or whichever slug is chosen) in AC2.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add an explicit prerequisite gate to AC #1 stating it can only be verified after stories 79da, 4dc0, and 1a51 have confirmed live signing, so the acceptance criterion is not ambiguously self-contained.","cohort":["COH","E1","T4"],"criteria":["COH","E1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":"novelty","evidence":["What section: 'after those three stories confirm signing, take a candidate anchor = current tickets HEAD and verify...'","AC #1: 'rebar verify-identity --all --require-authenticated --since <anchor> exits 0' — written with no conditionality on 79da/4dc0/1a51","Stories 79da, 4dc0, 1a51 are referenced as prerequisites for choosing the anchor but are not listed as formal dependencies or sequencing gates anywhere in the plan"],"finding":"AC #1's proving command ('rebar verify-identity --all --require-authenticated --since <anchor> exits 0') cannot be verified until stories 79da, 4dc0, and 1a51 confirm signing is live and the anchor SHA is chosen — but AC #1 is written as a self-contained, unconditional criterion with no mention of this prerequisite, creating an apparent contradiction between the What section (which makes the anchor decision contingent on three other stories) and the AC (which implies it can be verified as part of this story's own completion check).","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f0e0706ed1ff7003b","impact":0.33,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section, third bullet ('Decide and document the enforcement-boundary anchor') vs. Acceptance Criteria AC #1","norm_id":"n7128f53f3ec5e380","priority":0.165,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An implementer finishes the regression test (AC #2) and rebar.toml check (AC #3) but cannot close AC #1 because the three writer stories haven't completed yet — the story appears blocked at AC sign-off with no guidance on how to handle partial completion.","A reviewer sees AC #1 marked done before 79da/4dc0/1a51 are merged and cannot tell if the anchor was chosen correctly or speculatively."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Amend AC #1 to read: 'Once stories 79da, 4dc0, and 1a51 are merged and signing is confirmed live across all writers, `rebar verify-identity --all --require-authenticated --since <anchor>` exits 0. This AC is intentionally deferred until those stories land.' Alternatively, split this AC into a separate follow-on ticket that has 79da/4dc0/1a51 as formal blocking dependencies.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.5,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"low","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}}],"impact_model_version":"plan-v3","material_fingerprint":"f2f81bdfcdf914cb","metrics":{"claim_path":"no-llm/no-network (structural; the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify)","det_ms":201.1,"llm_calls":28,"llm_ms":319004.0,"total_ms":319354.9,"verify_requests":13},"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","regver":"b293b9a55de591cc","runner":"pydantic_ai","schema":"plan_review_result_v2","ticket_id":"8d91-5103-ae1b-44a7","ticket_type":"story","verdict":"BLOCK","verified_at_sha":"2165ee5cf60d83451c602a58cc7cd21619cb3b24"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"REVIEW_RESULT","timestamp":1784238101244786001,"uuid":"1019cab3-79dd-4a98-a341-5b521fd6b531"}